ation Review Centre and Resource Programs, Director, Executive Director related to the SRP. Participate in SRP committee meetings that may have an impact on Inquiry Centre communication. Provide feedback on web-page content and enhancements. Provide external feedback on the program to the SRP Executive Team; ensure key messaging is maintained for the Inquiry Centre.\n<br>\n<br>\nCommunicate and consult with the Executive Team and Communications as needed. Collect and prepare daily statistics for the Manger that includes how many email and phone inquiries received and responded and what is outstanding. Ensure SRP mailbox structure and SharePoint records adhere to records management policy. Reply to inquiries from the SRP mailbox and recorded voicemails. Reach out to subject matter experts to get technical or policy input as required. Forward questions to other teams that come to the inbox such as Site Nominations, ETS, Crown Land Data. Send notifications to applicants whose applications are declined. File approved grant agreements an inquiries in the mailbox folder for the appropriate team to review Send email updates to the SRP email contact list as necessary. Manage and maintain large distribution lists for sending out mass emails.<br>\n</ul>\n</div></div></div><br>\n<div></div><div><div><div>Qualifications<br>\n</div></div>\n</div><br>\n<div></div><div><div><div><div>University graduation in geology, engineering, law, commerce or accounting, or other related field plus 4 years of progressively related experience is required.<br>\n<br>\nDemonstrated understanding of grant programs, including knowledge of the legislation, regulations, and policies related to the SRP program. Demonstrated knowledge and experience of government decision-making processes, coupled with a thorough and broad understanding of energy industry and oil and gas sectors is required. Demonstrated experience with Microsoft Outlook, Excel, Word and SharePoint is required.<br>\n<br>\nDemonstrated a