es through the SRP application lifecycle, manage records and provide information for the Office of Auditor General (OAG) audits when required. The position will initiate, plan, organize and implement activities based on high-level direction and the intended outcomes, and prepare and provide information through briefing materials, presentations, memos and other forms of communication as required by the department. The position will also develop and maintain databases of the SRP Projects to ensure ongoing compliance to the program objectives, conduct research and gather information on potential issues, carry out appropriate analysis, and consult others when necessary. Contributing learnings to broader program development and implementation activities is also required.<br>\n</div>\n</div></div></div><br>\n<div></div><div><div><div>Qualifications<br>\n</div></div>\n</div><br>\n<div></div><div><div><div><div>University graduation in geology, engineering, law, commerce, accounting or related field, plus four (4) years of directly related experience is required.\n<br>\n<br>\nDemonstrated understanding of relevant grant regulations and legislation, as well as knowledge of program guidelines, program eligibility criteria, and funding structures if required. Demonstrated understanding of business planning, organizational structure, and strategic priorities, with the interest and ability to learn about the Department of Energy and the PPS Branch, is required. Knowledge of financial components of a project, grant evaluation and grant processing will be required, along with proven success using project management (PM) tools and techniques to process and track packages through the PM cycle.\n<br>\n<br>\nDemonstrated experience with Microsoft Office, particularly with Word and Excel, as well as experience with database development and maintenance is required.\n<br>\n<br>\nDemonstrated understanding of Alberta's regional planning system, legal principles of contracts and contract r