ure / systematic reviews by\n<ul><li>Drafting and submitting review protocols</li>\n<li>Working with a librarian to develop searches and inclusion and exclusion criteria</li>\n<li>Performing and leading title and abstract screening</li>\n<li>Performing full-text screening and analysis</li>\n</ul></li></ul></li><li>Teamwork and Stakeholder Engagement\n<ul><li>Establishes and maintains effective, productive relationships with staff, peers, immediate reports to manager and Principal Investigator within Department of Critical Care Medicine and outside of our department</li>\n<li>Ability to problem solve and make decisions in complex situations</li>\n<li>Strong communication and team skills, and an ability to exercise judgment within established guidelines</li>\n<li>Critical and innovative thinking abilities</li>\n<li>Time management and project management skills</li>\n</ul></li></ul><p><b>Qualifications / Requirements:</b></p><ul>\n<li>Bachelor degree in a health-related field is required</li>\n<li>Masters Degree in a health-related field is preferred</li>\n<li>Minimum 2 years of related experience</li>\n<li>Experience screening and consenting participants for research studies in a clinical environment is an asset</li>\n<li>Experience working with SPSS or STATA is an asset</li>\n<li>Qualitative research skills are an asset. Experience working with NVIVO or other qualitative software is an asset</li>\n<li>Experience in an intensive care unit or similar environment an asset</li>\n<li>Experience conducting literature reviews or knowledge of literature reviews are an asset</li>\n<li>Advanced skills in Microsoft Office Suite (Word, Outlook, Excel, PowerPoint) and EndNote</li>\n<li>Experience submitting human research ethics and Alberta Health Services approvals</li>\n<li>Knowledgeable around regulations for granting agencies (eg. Tri Council) and experience assisting in grant or studentship submission is an asset</li>\n<li>Demonstrated strong communication and team skills, a